BAUCHI – The Amalgamation of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Youth Organizations in the North-East geopolitical zone has endorsed Senator Halliru Dauda Jika as its gubernatorial candidate in Bauchi state ahead of the 2023 general elections. The organization which is under the auspices of the APC Northeast Youth Ambassadors outlined the reasons behind its endorsement of Senator Halliru Jika to contest the state’s most coveted office in the next polls. The Zonal Chairman of the organization, Mr Abubakar Abdulmumin during a press briefing yesterday in Bauchi, recalled that Senator Jika now representing Bauchi central district in the Senate had been elected four times to various elective offices to represent the electorates in the state and Nigeria. -Advertisement- He said Jika was a one-time member and speaker of the Bauchi State House of Assembly and subsequently a member who represented the Ganjuwa/Darazo federal constituency in the National Assembly. “It is for these reasons and many more that we members of the APC have come to the conclusion that Senator Halliru Jika is the only politician from the Bauchi central senatorial district and the state, that can effectively steer the ship of Bauchi in the 2023 polls”, Abubakar said. Abubakar recalled that some of those APC members aspiring for the governorship position in the state have in the 2019 general elections were alleged to have carried out anti-party activities that resulted in the enthronement of the People’s Democratic Party collect back governance of the state, hence they should now not be given the opportunity to re-contest the seat. He explained that the moment those betrayals are given another opportunity again to contest elections, they will exhibit the same attitude, which will eventually make the party lose, pointing out that a leopard hardly changes its spots.